                <h3 class="card-title">Mormon Pioneer National Historic Trail</h3>
                <br/>
                <p>Explore the Mormon Pioneer National Historic Trail across five states to see the 1,300-mile route traveled by Mormons who fled Nauvoo, Illinois, to the Great Salt Lake Valley in 1846-1847.</p>
                <div class="accordion" id="accordionExample">
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingZero">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseZero" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseZero">
                                Directions
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseZero" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingZero" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                <p class="fst-italic">The Mormon Pioneer National Historic Trail crosses five states following the route the Pioneer Company of 1846-1847 established from Nauvoo, Illinois, to Salt Lake City, Utah, covering about 1,300 miles.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
